headline: DAT: Truckload volumes held steady in July as summer seasonality peaks
summary: BEAVERTON, Ore., August 15, 2025--Truckload freight volumes held steady in July as summer seasonality took hold, driven by produce and retail goods moving ahead of the Independence Day holiday, said DAT Freight & Analytics, which operates the DAT One freight marketplace and DAT iQ data analytics service. Volumes softened gradually through the rest of the month.
